German Banks Cancel U.S. Securities Deposit Accounts, FTD Says

-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 
2011-12-13T21:20:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-13/german-banks-cancel-u-s-securities-deposit-accounts-ftd-says.html
German lenders including  Deutsche
Bank AG (DBK)  and  UniCredit SpA (UCG) ’s German division are canceling
securities deposit accounts with U.S. customers after new
regulations in the country led to higher costs,  Financial Times
Deutschland  reported in a preview of an article to appear in
tomorrow’s edition, without saying where it got the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
